      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/4/20/15",
      "text": [
        ": سَأَلْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنِ اَلْمَمْلُوكَةِ تَكُونُ تَحْتَ اَلْعَبْدِ ثُمَّ تُعْتَقُ قَالَ \"تُخَيَّرُ فَإِنْ شَاءَتْ أَقَامَتْ عَلَى زَوْجِهَا وَ إِنْ شَاءَتْ بَانَتْ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.4873 - Ḥariz ibn ʿAbdillah narrated from Muḥammad ibn Muslim who said:\nI asked Abu Abdullah (as) about a bondwoman who was married to a slave man and then she was freed.\nImam (as) said: \"She has the choice; if she wishes, she may remain with her husband, and if she wishes, she may separate from him.\""
        ]
      }
    },
